{
  "id": "jsonbored_metagraphed_790",
  "repo_name": "jsonbored/metagraphed",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/jsonbored/metagraphed",
  "base_commit": "98849f0435173a2fdecf28faf68eedafd5bbf940",
  "pr_number": 790,
  "issue_number": 750,
  "issue_title": "TypeScript SDK: retries, ETag caching, convenience methods",
  "issue_body": "Part of #740 \u00b7 Phase 3 (SDK / DX).\n\n## Context\nThe TS client (`packages/client`, npm `@jsonbored/metagraphed`) is fully typed from OpenAPI but lacks retries/backoff, response caching/ETag conditional requests, and ergonomic convenience methods.\n\n## Scope\n**In:** (1) opt-in **retries/backoff** on 429/5xx (honor Retry-After); (2) optional **ETag-based conditional caching** (\u2192 304); (3) convenience builders (`client.subnets({limit})` / `client.getSubnet(7)`) + `.fetchAll()`.\n**Out:** Breaking the typed core; mandatory new deps.\n\n## Completion requirements (a PR MUST satisfy ALL)\n- [ ] Retries/backoff (opt-in) honoring Retry-After; tested\n- [ ] ETag conditional-request caching (opt-in); tested\n- [ ] Convenience methods + auto-pagination helper; types preserved\n- [ ] Backward compatible + tree-shakeable; tests + typecheck pass\n- [ ] README/examples updated; version bump + changelog\n- [ ] Conventional Commit title\n\n## Notes\nThe typed surface is generated from OpenAPI \u2014 don't hand-edit generated types.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-16T07:56:56.000Z",
  "test_cmd": [
    "npm",
    "test",
    "--",
    "--passWithNoTests"
  ],
